<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="41" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="42.[192,1440,898,1050]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,302,898,922]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Ecology</emphasis>
. Lowland, montane. Epigean. Edges of trickles, seepages, puddles, flats along roadsides and rivers, as well as stream banks, at a certain distance (
<quantity box="[857,948,929,954]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="41" unit="m" value="9.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="3.0">3–15 m</quantity>
) from water.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[192,1440,898,1050]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
Open ground; wet, usually sandy, sometimes clay, bare or sparsely vegetated soil. Nocturnal; hides during the day at the base of plants (e.g., 
<taxonomicName box="[710,799,994,1017]" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="42" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[710,799,994,1017]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Juncus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), under fallen leaves and plant debris, as well as in moss, under stones and soil clods. Gregarious.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[192,1440,1089,1178]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,297,1089,1113]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Biology</emphasis>
. Seasonality: September, November–January, March, May–June. Tenerals: December–January. Occasionally infested with fungi (Laboulbeniales). Defence mechanism: when alarmed, the adult escapes by running.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[192,1440,1217,1274]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,416,1217,1242]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Dispersal power</emphasis>
. Macropterous, probably capable of flight. Moderate runner. Vagility likely favoured by flight capacity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[192,1176,1313,1338]" box="[192,1176,1313,1338]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,493,1313,1337]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Collecting techniques</emphasis>
. Turning plant leaves and debris, stones and soil clods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[192,1440,1377,1434]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,332,1377,1401]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Reference</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Larochelle, A. &amp; M. - C. Lariviere" box="[345,754,1378,1402]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 281" refId="ref33655" refString="Larochelle, A., and M. - C. Lariviere. 2001. Carabidae (Insecta: Coleoptera): catalogue. Fauna of New Zealand 43: 1 - 281." type="journal article" year="2001">Larochelle and Larivière 2001: 83</bibRefCitation>
(catalogue; biology, dispersal power, ecology, geographic distribution, reference).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[192,1440,1474,1530]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,303,1474,1498]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Remark</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lindroth, C. H." box="[320,516,1474,1498]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41" pagination="161 - 198" refId="ref33972" refString="Lindroth, C. H. 1976. Genus Bembidion Latreille (Coleoptera: Carabidae) in New Zealand: a revision. New Zealand Journal of Zoology 3: 161 - 198." type="journal article" year="1976">Lindroth (1976)</bibRefCitation>
